 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
18. Section 1357.40 is revised to read as follows: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;1357.40 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Direct payments to Indian Tribal Organizations (title IV&hyph;B, subpart 1, child welfare services). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Who may apply for direct funding?
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Any Indian Tribal Organization (ITO) that meets the definitions in section 428(c) of the Act, or any consortium or
other group of eligible tribal organizations authorized by the membership of the tribes to act for them is eligible
to apply for direct funding if: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) The Indian tribe (or tribes comprising the ITO) is providing, under a contract (or grant) with the Secretary of
the Interior under section 102 of the Indian Self-Determination Act (25 U.S.C. 450f) child welfare services which
would otherwise be provided directly by the Secretary of the Interior; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The Indian tribe, consortium or group has a plan for child welfare services provided by the ITO that is jointly developed
by the Indian Tribal Organization and the Department. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Title IV&hyph;B Child and Family Services Plan (CFSP)
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
. (1) In order to receive funds under title IV&hyph;B, subpart 1, beginning in FY 1995, the Indian tribe or tribal organization
must have in effect an approved five-year child and family services plan that meets the applicable requirements of
&sect;1357.15 of this part. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The Indian tribe or tribal organization must also comply with section 422 of the Act; 45 CFR part 1355 (except that
the requirements in &sect;1355.30 for a single State agency and Governor's review of the CFSP do not apply); and other
applicable requirements of section 1357 of this part. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Information related to the requirements of Section 427 of the Act.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The following information must be submitted along with the assurances required to be eligible for title IV&hyph;B,
subpart 1 funds: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) A statement of the legal responsibility, if any, for children who are in foster care on the reservation and those
awaiting adoption; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) A description of tribal jurisdiction in civil and criminal matters, existence or nonexistence of a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
tribal court and the type of court and codes, if any; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) An identification of the standards for foster family homes and institutional care and day care; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) The Indian tribal organization's political subdivisions, if any; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) Whether the tribal organization is controlled, sanctioned or chartered by the governing body of Indians to be
served and if so, documentation of that fact; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(6) Any limitations on authorities granted to the Indian tribal organizations; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(7) The tribal resolution(s) authorizing an application for a direct title IV&hyph;B, subpart 1 grant under this
Part. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

